The paper discusses knowledge graph embedding, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) for downstream tasks such as question answering and recommendation. The paper also involves manipulating data in a graph (cs.DB) and discusses adversarial attacks (cs.CR) on the embeddings. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed attack strategies on two benchmarks, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR).
